This paper belongs to the sub-category of AI called Neural Networks. 

Explanation: The paper proposes a new type of neural network called Case Retrieval Nets (CRNs) and discusses their foundations, properties, and implementation. The paper describes how CRNs are trained using backpropagation and how they can be used for case-based reasoning. The paper also presents experimental results demonstrating the effectiveness of CRNs in solving various problems. Therefore, the paper is primarily focused on the use of neural networks for case-based reasoning.
